# Loading skeletons — structural fidelity

Skeletons must be **pixel-structure faithful** to the UI they replace. A loading state that looks like a different screen (or a generic gray block) is a bug.

Use `@/components/ui/skeleton` for every placeholder. Full patterns for tables and empty states remain in `DAPP.mdc`; this rule owns loading fidelity.

---

## Required principles

1. **1:1 layout match** — Same wrappers, `className`s, breakpoints, grids/flex, padding, gaps, and visible region count as the loaded UI.
2. **Correct state** — Skeletonize what the user sees on first load (e.g. profile **view** card, not the edit form).
3. **Variants** — If the loaded UI changes by prop/type (`single-release` vs `multi-release`, `size="lg"`), the skeleton accepts equivalent props or mirrors the active variant.
4. **No generic blocks** — Forbidden: a lone `Skeleton className="h-48 w-full"` or raw `div` with `bg-muted` when the real UI has cards, rows, avatars, badges, or tables. Match each visible region.
5. **Always `Skeleton`** — Use `@/components/ui/skeleton`; do not invent structural placeholders with muted backgrounds alone.
6. **Dual layout** — If loaded UI has cards `md:hidden` + table `hidden md:block`, the skeleton renders **both** with the same split.
7. **Co-location** — Define the skeleton in the same file **above** the main export, or in a sibling `*Skeleton.tsx` in the same feature `ui/` folder when size requires a split.
8. **List count** — Repeat 3–5 rows/cards with the same gap/padding as loaded content.

---

## Do / Don't

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — wrong state (edit form while default is view)
<CardContent className="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <Skeleton className="h-10 w-full" />
  <Skeleton className="h-10 w-full" />
</CardContent>

// ✅ GOOD — mirrors ProfileDetailsCard (avatar + text + footer)
<CardContent>
  <div className="flex items-center gap-4">
    <Skeleton className="size-16 rounded-xl" />
    <div className="space-y-2">
      <Skeleton className="h-5 w-40" />
      <Skeleton className="h-4 w-32" />
    </div>
  </div>
</CardContent>
<CardContent className="mt-auto flex justify-end pt-0">
  <Skeleton className="h-3 w-40" />
</CardContent>
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — generic muted grid unrelated to DashboardView
<div className="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 *:min-h-42 *:bg-muted" />

// ✅ GOOD — same shell as loaded: columns, card regions, chart heights
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 lg:grid-cols-[.68fr_.32fr]">
  {/* left: stats + chart h-60 md:h-72 + … */}
  {/* right: gauge + lists */}
</div>
```

---

## Review checklist

Before merging skeleton work:

- [ ] Same breakpoints and column counts as loaded UI
- [ ] Same avatar / icon / button sizes
- [ ] Headers include action placeholders when the loaded UI has actions
- [ ] Footers / metadata rows present when the loaded UI has them
- [ ] Correct data variant (release type, sidebar size, etc.)
- [ ] No unused / dead skeleton exports
- [ ] Dual mobile cards + desktop table when applicable

---

## Example (dual layout)

```tsx
const MembersTableSkeleton = () => (
  <>
    <div className="flex flex-col gap-3 md:hidden">
      {Array.from({ length: 3 }).map((_, index) => (
        <Card key={index}>
          <CardHeader className="flex flex-row items-start justify-between gap-3 pb-3">
            <Skeleton className="h-5 w-32" />
            <div className="flex gap-1">
              <Skeleton className="size-8 rounded-md" />
              <Skeleton className="size-8 rounded-md" />
            </div>
          </CardHeader>
          <CardContent className="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <div className="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <Skeleton className="h-3 w-12" />
              <Skeleton className="h-4 w-24" />
            </div>
          </CardContent>
        </Card>
      ))}
    </div>
    <div className="hidden md:block">
      <Table>
        <TableHeader>{/* same columns as MembersTable */}</TableHeader>
        <TableBody>
          {Array.from({ length: 5 }).map((_, index) => (
            <TableRow key={index}>
              <TableCell>
                <Skeleton className="h-4 w-24" />
              </TableCell>
              {/* one Skeleton per cell */}
            </TableRow>
          ))}
        </TableBody>
      </Table>
    </div>
  </>
);
```
